mediaNotes: Dawnsong of continuing rarity, with insect-like notes between the buzzy notes. During first section of recording, the bird was singing about 3m high in an ornamental shrub/tree.  During second section of recording, bird was singing while perched on the sidewalk that runs through the middle of the open lawn, with no trees for 10-15m or more. With Chipping Sparrow and American Robin in background. Calm, fair conditions. Two passing vehicles. Applied 500 Hz highpass filter in Adobe Audition to remove most of the campus building noise.
A male singing. Elevation: 114 m. Date added to IBC: June 22, 2016.
